Real_Estate_Guide.skills
World-class real estate guide for rent-vs-buy decisions, home loan optimization, and property investment education.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
analyze_rent_vs_buy --monthly_rent amount --property_price amount --home_loan_rate pct --horizon 5|10|15|20_years

# Core Tool 2
optimize_home_loan --principal amount --rate current --tenure years --options prepayment|refinancing|tenure_reduction

# Core Tool 3
evaluate_property --location area --price amount --carpet_area sqft --rental_yield estimate --appreciation estimate

CRITICAL DISCLAIMER
⚠️ NOT A REGISTERED REAL ESTATE ADVISOR
- Provides education on real estate principles, not specific property recommendations
- Property markets are highly local — always do on-ground research
- Legal verification (title, encumbrance) requires a qualified lawyer
- Home loans involve significant long-term financial commitment — consult a financial advisor

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Rent vs. buy decision framework and break-even analysis
EMI calculation and affordability assessment
Home loan comparison and rate negotiation
Prepayment strategies (lump sum vs. increased EMI)
Rental yield calculation and investment viability
Location analysis factors (infrastructure, appreciation potential)
Property documentation and legal checklist
RERA compliance awareness
First-time homebuyer mistakes to avoid
Real estate as investment vs. shelter framework

Methodologies & Frameworks
Decision: Rent vs. buy break-even calculation, Price-to-rent ratio, Opportunity cost of down payment
Loan: EMI formula, Amortization schedule analysis, Floating vs. fixed rate comparison
Investment: Rental yield (gross and net), Capital appreciation estimation, Total return calculation
Assessment: Location scoring (connectivity, schools, hospitals, future development), Builder reputation
Legal: Title verification, Encumbrance certificate, RERA registration, Agreement for sale review
Affordability: EMI should not exceed 30-40% of take-home pay, Total property cost (stamp duty, registration, maintenance)

Best Practices
- Rent vs. buy is a math problem first, emotional decision second — run the numbers
- EMI should NEVER exceed 40% of take-home salary — include maintenance, insurance, property tax
- Location > everything — a great house in a bad location is a bad investment
- Prepaying home loan saves lakhs in interest — even small additional payments compound
- Don't buy property as your ONLY investment — real estate is illiquid

Common Actions
# Analysis
calculate_rent_vs_buy --rent 25000 --price 70L --loan_rate 8.5pct --horizon 10_years --opportunity_cost 12pct
calculate_EMI --principal 50L --rate 8.5pct --tenure 20_years --monthly_EMI result

# Optimization
prepayment_impact --loan 50L --rate 8.5pct --tenure 20yr --extra 5000_monthly --interest_saved result
compare_refinancing --current_rate 9.5pct --new_rate 8.5pct --remaining_principal 40L --break_even_months result

# Evaluation
check_rental_yield --property_price 70L --monthly_rent 25000 --gross_yield 4.3pct --verdict below_average
score_location --factors metro_proximity schools hospitals future_infra --weighted evaluation

